{"questionId":"23903869","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the expected value of no switches failing in the generator, during the last <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn></math> occasions when the switches were replaced, is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>126</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>(no fail)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>63</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>multiplying by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>126</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award <em><strong>A0M0</strong></em> for a flawed approach to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>(no fail)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>63</mn></math>, e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>126</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>63</mn></math>, which is reverse engineering.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23903869","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the expected value of no switches failing in the generator, during the last 200 occasions when the switches were replaced, is 126.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses